---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Pintos OS & WACC Compiler — Abhivir Singh"
  description="Built an operating system and compiler from scratch. Best in cohort of 230 at Imperial College London."
>
  <div class="editorial-container">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-16 border-b border-border">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="tag-pill">C</span>
        <span class="tag-pill">ARM Assembly</span>
        <span class="tag-pill">Systems Programming</span>
        <span class="tag-pill">Best in Cohort</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground leading-[1.1] mb-4">
        Pintos OS & WACC Compiler
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-6">
        Built an <span class="text-foreground font-medium">operating system</span> and a
        <span class="text-foreground font-medium">compiler</span> from scratch.
        Best in cohort of 230 students at Imperial.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        These two projects were the hardest and most rewarding things I did at university.
        Not just technically — they taught me how to lead a team under extreme pressure,
        how to build deep trust with collaborators, and why Paul Graham says doing hard
        projects is the precursor to doing a startup.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Pintos -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-border">
      <p class="section-label">Pintos — Operating System</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Pintos is a teaching operating system written in C. We implemented it from
            the ground up: thread scheduling, user program execution, virtual memory with
            page fault handling, and a file system with buffer caching.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Every component had to work together — a bug in the scheduler could crash the
            filesystem, a memory leak in the VM would corrupt user programs. Building
            something where <span class="text-foreground font-medium">every layer depends
            on every other layer</span> teaches you systems thinking that no course can.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">threads</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Priority scheduling with donation, alarm clock, multi-level feedback queue</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">userprog</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Argument passing, system calls, process execution and termination</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">vm</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Supplemental page table, frame table, swap partition, memory-mapped files</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">filesys</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Indexed and extensible files, subdirectories, buffer cache</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WACC -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-border">
      <p class="section-label">WACC — Compiler</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            WACC is a simple imperative language. We built a compiler that takes WACC source
            code and produces ARM assembly — lexer, parser, semantic analyser, and code
            generator. Every stage hand-written, no parser generators.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            The compiler handles expressions, control flow, functions, arrays, pairs,
            heap allocation, and register allocation. Getting the code generator right —
            where abstract syntax becomes real machine instructions — is where the deep
            learning happens.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">frontend</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Lexer, recursive descent parser, AST construction, type checking and semantic analysis</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">backend</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">ARM assembly code generation, register allocation, stack frame management</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-border py-4 grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
          <div class="col-span-3 md:col-span-2"><span class="tag-pill">target</span></div>
          <div class="col-span-9 md:col-span-10">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">WACC source &rarr; ARM assembly &rarr; executable binary</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why This Matters -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-16">
      <p class="section-label">Why This Matters</p>
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Paul Graham writes that doing hard projects with talented people is the best
          precursor to doing a startup. These projects were exactly that. The people I
          built these with are now potential co-founders — we've been through the kind
          of pressure that reveals what someone is actually like to work with.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Top marks out of 230 students. But the real output wasn't the grade — it was
          learning that I can lead a team through something genuinely hard, that I can
          hold the whole system in my head, and that I'm at my best when the stakes are high.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
